Use scons to compile both the tigre library and the earth sample:

SCons
=====

Compiling (using SConstruct):
$> scons

Target a project only:
$> scons -f tigre.py

Cleaning:
$> scons -c

Cleaning a project only:
$> scons -f tigre.py -c

Build Tigre
===========

$> scons

GLFW
====

$> scons

Qt
==

Generate the Makefile and compile the project:
$> qmake && make

Cleaning:
$> make clean 
or
$> make distclean

Android
=======

/!\ Requires Android sdk and ndk /!\

Update the project (path, sdk target, name):
$> android update project -p . -t 1 -n "Earth"

Building everything:
$> ndk-build

Installing quickly:
$> ant debug install